I"<p>I recently read an article, “<a href="https://hbr.org/2016/09/know-your-customers-jobs-to-be-done">Know Your Customers’ ‘Jobs to Be Done’</a>”</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>When we buy a product, we essentially “hire” it to help us do a job. If it does the job well, we hire it again. If it does a crummy job, we “fire” it and look for something else to solve the problem.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>this</p>

<p>Billboards along the peninsula are filled with “AI-powered” this and that for pretty much all SaaS companies.</p>

